To create MIPS binaries from C or assembler code the mipsel gcc cross-compiler is required.
For installation on Debian or Ubuntu from emdebian.org do the following:


1. Add the repository key:

apt-get install emdebian-archive-keyring 


2. Add the repository to sources.list

Add the following lines to /etc/apt/sources.list or create /etc/apt/sources.list.d/emdebian.list containing the following lines:

#
# -- Emdebian cross toolchains
deb http://www.emdebian.org/debian/ testing main


3. Update repositories

apt-get update


4. Install mipsel-Compiler

apt-get install g++-4.4-mipsel-linux-gnu g++-4.4-multilib-mipsel-linux-gnu gcc-4.4-mipsel-linux-gnu gcc-4.4-multilib-mipsel-linux-gnu


